<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-19T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-19T07:00:00-05:00" n="188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4597: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Magruder</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-19T13:00:00+01:00">July 19, 1931—1
                                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:25 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                                <p>24. Department’s telegram No. 14, July 3, 2 p.m. Yesterday,
                                    Portuguese Government acceded to British invitation to adopt
                                    Hoover proposal but made reservations in respect of reparations
                                    in kind and refrained from any public announcement.</p>
                                <p>Under the circumstances does the Department still desire delivery
                                    of message?</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Magruder</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>